cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of NOMA on MEC offloading, which involves wireless communication and network architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper develops analytical results to demonstrate the efficiency of NOMA in reducing latency and energy consumption, which involves information theory. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the coexistence of two communication techniques, which involves distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the impact of users' channel conditions and transmit powers on the application of NOMA to MEC, which involves control systems. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper provides computer simulation results to evaluate the performance of NOMA-MEC, which involves multimedia applications.
